    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-08-04T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-08-04T14:00:00-05:00" n="235"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d235">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.48/1609: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-08-04T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 4, 1938—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following for Tokyo: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“268, August 4, 3 p.m. Your 509, August 2, 9 p.m.,<note n="50"
                                xml:id="d235fn50">Not printed.</note> in regard to refugee zones at
                            Hankow and Wuchang.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>Your action in making available to the Foreign Office the text of
                                the communication from the Refugee Zone Committee is
                                approved.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>The Department desires that American officials scrupulously avoid
                                any responsibility to the Chinese or Japanese for the observance by
                                either of assurances given by the other in connection with the
                                establishment of refugee zones.</item>
                            <label>3.</label>
                            <item>On the other hand, the Department would not wish to take the
                                position of discouraging any attempt by private individuals to
                                procure the establishment of safety zones.</item>
                            <label>4.</label>
                            <item>With the above considerations in mind the Department desires that
                                American officials in China and Japan, in their discretion, extend
                                appropriate informal and unofficial assistance to the Wuhan Refugee
                                Zone Committee.”</item>
                        </list>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Repeat to Hankow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
